%N A394926 Numbers k such that sigma(k) = psi(k) + tau(k) + Omega(k)^7.
%C A394926 This sequence contains 136086*p^2 where p is prime such that gcd(136086, p) = 1 and is therefore infinite. Proof: sigma(136086*p^2) = 279984*(p^2 + p + 1) = 279984*(p^2 + p) + 48 + 279936 = psi(136086*p^2) + tau(136086*p^2) + bigomega(136086*p^2)^7. - _David A. Corneth_, Apr 07 2026
%C A394926 Is there any term other than a(1) not of this form, 2*3*37*613*p^2, with p <> {2, 3, 37, 613} ? - _M. F. Hasler_, Apr 08 2026
%e A394926 341375 is a term since sigma(341375) = 426192 = 409800 + 8 + 4^7 = psi(341375) + tau(341375) + Omega(341375)^7.
%o A394926 (PARI) isok(k) = {my(f = factor(k)); sigma(f) == prod(i=1, #f~, (f[i, 1]+1) * f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-1)) + numdiv(f) + bigomega(f)^7; } \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 07 2026
